Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Data by country, area, or territory for 12 Apr 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20Apr12_1618337587.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 34.7% of daily case numbers and 60.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 58.17 million cases. The USA reported over 80 000 cases over the last 24 hours followed by Brazil with 71 832 cases, Argentina (19 419), Colombia (14 509), and Peru with 11 248 cases. 7 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Mexico, Chile, Paraguay, Uruguay, Venezuela, Canada, and Ecuador). 5 countries (Dominican Republic, Cuba, El Salvador, Bolivia, and Honduras) reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 26.9% of daily case numbers and 20.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 47.72 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Spain, Belgium, Sweden, Switzerland , and Kazakhstan, among others. Turkey reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by France, Italy, Germany, and Poland, reporting more than 10 000 new cases in the past 24 hours. Another 12 countries reported more than 1000 cases, and an additional 8 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.1% of daily case numbers and 6.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.11 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (21 063) over the last 24 hours, followed by Iraq, Pakistan, Oman, Jordan, Lebanon, Palestinian Authority, UAE, Tunisia, Bahrain, and Kuwait. Qatar, Libya, Saudi Arabia, and Egypt, reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 0.8% of daily case numbers and 1.2 % of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 3.17 million cases. Ethiopia (1741) reported the highest number of cases over last 24 hours. South Africa reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Cameroon, Ghana, Mozambique, and Botswana, among others, did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 2.6% of daily case numbers and 1.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 2.09 million cases. Philippines reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 11 000 cases), followed by Japan, Malaysia, Mongolia, South Korea, Cambodia, and Papua New Guinea.

- The South East Asia region reported 26.7% of the daily newly reported cases and 9.1% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 16.35 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 168 000 cases, followed by Bangladesh (5819), Indonesia (4127) cases), Thailand, Nepal, and Sri Lanka.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 12 Apr 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

