[In the past 24 hours, India (160 694), Turkey (54 562), the USA (56 522), and Brazil (38 866), and have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 9350 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (late 10 Apr 2021 to late 11 Apr 2021). Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (13 countries) include India, Turkey, the USA, Brazil, Iran (23 311), Argentina (19 437), Colombia (16 739), Poland (11 989), Germany (11 523), Philippines (11 365), and Canada (10 858). A total of 50 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 24 of the 50 countries are from the European region, 9 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 3 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 12.9%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 2.8%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the USA show a 9.7% increase in daily reported cases and a 7.8% increase in reported deaths.

Impression: The global daily reported over 600 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours with over 137.25 million cumulative reported cases and over 2.95 million reported deaths - Mod.UBA]
